in.tamchow.fractal.math.symbolics

Class Operable<T extends Operable<T,E>,E extends Derivable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.tamchow.fractal.math.symbolics.Derivable
      • in.tamchow.fractal.math.symbolics.Operable<T,E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Derivable>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Function, Polynomial

    public abstract class Operable<T extends Operable<T,E>,E extends Derivable>
extends Derivable
    Denotes a symbolic mathematical entity which supports certain operations.

    Note:

    Also, the add(Operable), subtract(Operable), multiply(Operable) and divide(Operable) only work with Operables of the same type. That is, only a Function can be operated with a Function, and only a Polynomial can be operated with a Polynomial.
